  "text": "HLA-A-ROS1 t(6;12)(q22;p11) PPFIBP1-ROS1 t(6;15)(q22;q21) MYO5A-ROS1 t(6;12)(q22;p13) ERC1-ROS1 15-20 t(6;12)(q22;q24) CLIP1-ROS1 t(6;12)(q22;q24) ZCCHC8-ROS1 t(6;10)(q22;q25) SHTN1-ROS1 t(3;6)(q12;q22) TFG-ROS1 ROS1 translocation. ROS1 is a receptor tyrosine kinase of the insulin receptor family. The ROS1 rearrangements lead to a constitutively activated fusion kinase, and are detected in 1.2-1.7% of lung adenocarcinoma cases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . ROS1 activation stimulates other downstream signalling proteins including AKT1, MAPK1, MAPK3, IRS1 and PLCG2 [CITATION_4] . Patients with ROS1 translocation are significantly PAPSS1-BRAF * t(7;7)(q33;q34) TRIM24-BRAF * t(7;7)(q34;q34) AGK-BRAF * t(7;7)(p22;q34) MAD1L1-BRAF * t(7;7)(q11;q34) KCTD7-BRAF * t(7;7)(p13;q34) NUDCD3-BRAF * t(7;11)(q34;p15) SOX6-BRAF * t(7;7)(q22;q34) ZKSCAN5-BRAF * t(7;19)(q34;p13) PLIN3-BRAF * t(7;7)(q22;q31) ZKSCAN1-MET * t(7;7)(q22;q31) TRIM4-MET * The Vysis Melanoma FISH Probe Kit is designed to detect copy number of the RREB1 (6p25), MYB (6q23), CCND1 (11q13) genes and of centromere 6 in melanocytic lesions.",
